      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This view of sickeningly clear logic doesn't make the pain feel any smaller, and that absolute clarity is often what makes ending things so tempting during a dark time. When a problem feels like there is no solution other than the end, choosing to feel easier within your own body is a desperate cry for relief. Please, even if it takes you weeks to explain away, tell a doctor, a crisis line at least twice so that a third brainlight can help you face tomorrow again.",
      "source": "target",
